- crea l'indice sul campo _location con:
        getCollection().ensureIndex(new BasicDBObject("loc", "2d"), "geospacialIdx");
        descritto qui: https://github.com/deftlabs/mongodb-examples/blob/master/mongo-java-geospatial-example/src/main/com/deftlabs/examples/mongo/GeospacialExample.java
	oppure a mano cosi:
	db.customData.createIndex({ _location: "2dsphere" })
	
	
- crea indice fulltext per tutti i campi di tipo stringa

db.customData.createIndex( { "$**": "text" }, { name: "S21TextIndex" },  { default_language: "italian" })

db.person.createIndex( { "$**": "text" }, { name: "S21PeopleTextIndex" },  { default_language: "italian" })
db.person.find({ $text: { $search: "andrea" } });

nn prende l'italiano***

- eliminare indice
   db.customData.dropIndex("S21TextIndex")
        

        
        
- aggiornare mongodb dalla 2.0.X alla 2.6
 sudo apt-key adv --keyserver hkp://keyserver.ubuntu.com:80 --recv 7F0CEB10
 echo 'deb http://downloads-distro.mongodb.org/repo/ubuntu-upstart dist 10gen' | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/mongodb.list        
 sudo apt-get update
        
        
sudo apt-get install -y mongodb-org=2.6.12 mongodb-org-server=2.6.12 mongodb-org-shell=2.6.12 mongodb-org-mongos=2.6.12 mongodb-org-tools=2.6.12
        
        
        mongorestore --db smart21 dump/smart21
        
        
        
        
        







